Since $\triangle ABC$ is isosceles, angles $\angle ABC$ and $\angle ACB$ are equal. Let $x = \angle ABC = \angle ACB$. Then $\angle BAC = 180^\circ - 2x$. Since $OB = OC$ (radii of the circumcircle), $\triangle OBC$ is isosceles. Let $y = \angle OBC = \angle OCB$. Then $\angle BOC = 180^\circ - 2y$.

